      <div class="text-xl py-1">Hey there ðŸ‘‹</div>
      <div class="text-5xl font-bold">I'm Cuong!</div>
      <div class="text-3xl py-3 font-bold">PhD Student @ The University of Texas at Dallas</div>

      <text class="text-lg">
        <p>
          I am a PhD Student at <a class="link" target="_blank" href="https://www.utdallas.edu/">The University of Texas at Dallas</a>, working under the supervision of <a class="link" target="_blank" href="https://personal.utdallas.edu/~tien.n.nguyen/">Prof. Tien N. Nguyen</a>. My research focuses on three interconnected areas:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc mx-6 my-2 space-y-1">
          <li>Applying <b>AI/ML</b> to <b>software engineering tasks</b> at the <b>large-scale repository level</b></li>
          <li>Exploring <b>if and how Large Language Models (LLMs) understand and reason about program behavior</b></li>
          <li>And then building <b>code world models</b> that can capture <b>program dynamic behavior better</b> and <b>optimize software development processes</b></li>
        </ul>
        <p class="py-2">
          Previously, I was a full-time researcher in the <a class="link" target="_blank" href="https://fpt.com/en/news/fpt-news/fpt-software-ai-center">FPT AI Residency Program</a>, a prestigious talent program for young Vietnamese researchers that spans 2 years. The program offers access to high-performance computing resources and world-class mentorship, with a focus on publishing in top-tier venues with a competitive acceptance rate of ~3-4%.
        </p>
      </text>
    </div>

    <!-- RIGHT: headshot -->
